    narrator "{i}She leaves before Vesper can respond.{/i}"
    narrator "{i}The observation deck settles into silence. Stars. Scratched viewport. The sound of a ship moving toward something it doesn't yet understand.{/i}"
    narrator "{i}Vesper stays. Watching the dark. Thinking about Pol's children, who will receive a form. Thinking about the workers in the mine, who receive forms every day. Thinking about the difference between systems that kill quickly and systems that kill slowly, and how neither kind ever apologizes.{/i}"

